track_notes: Hiked in 2022 July. Pear Butte Trail 979 desperately needs some serious maintenance. Large trees blocking mainly at lower elevations, sometimes difficult to get over them with heavy pack. Bismark Peak Trail 983 is no longer officially maintained, but it is not in bad shape. However it is easy to lose it and wander off to game trails. This track has many of that so probably best not totally follow it. It is my down climb as I looped this from Mt. Aix trail. Last push to summit is very bad steep, loose talus. No summit register present. There are 2 bivy spots on the summit.

Hiked in 2022 July. The ridge traverse starts out very pleasant and easy. However, soon there are difficult sections and it will slow you down significantly. Probably the worst is the slopes above Carmelita Basin. It is very loose scree and talus. I slid down there many times, crossing that section is very bad. There might be a better route to avoid that bit. Took me almost 6 hours to summit with a light pack in running shoes. I would use boots if have to do again. I would say it is better to take the other route, esp. with a heavy pack.
